s publication through publication at IJBAS. IJBAS requires to provide worldwide forum for communication between researchers, experts, professionals, and policymakers to exchanging researches, views, concerns, as well as innovative ideas and lastest issues in the form of original papers. Please send your manuscript to the following email below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:editor@insikapub.com\">editor@insikapub.com</a> and <a href=\"mailto:insanakademika@yahoo.com\">insanakademika@yahoo.com</a>','Call for Paper','','publish','open','open','','call-for-paper','','','2014-12-22 00:41:34','2014-12-22 00:41:34','',54,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=49',0,'page','',0),(50,1,'2014-12-22 00:36:26','2014-12-22 00:36:26','<h2 class=\"item-page-title\">Call for Paper</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIJBAS welcomes research scholars, scientists, and professionals from different domains in its realm of on-line and open access publication through publication at IJBAS. IJBAS requires to provide worldwide forum for communication between researchers, experts, professionals, and policymakers to exchanging researches, views, concerns, as well as innovative ideas and lastest issues in the form of original papers. Please send your manuscript to the following email below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:editor@insikapub.com\">editor@insikapub.com</a> and <a href=\"mailto:insanakademika@yahoo.com\">insanakademika@yahoo.com</a>','Call for Paper','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-v1','','','2014-12-22 00:36:26','2014-12-22 00:36:26','',49,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=50',0,'revision','',0),(51,1,'2014-12-22 00:37:09','2014-12-22 00:37:09','<h2 class=\"item-page-title\">Author Guideline</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor preparation of Paper Submission please read the following guide to prepare for your paper.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Submission of papers</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPlease prepare your manuscripts in English language. Either British and American English are accepted but be consistent in spelling and usage throughout the article and avoid mixing the both. Before submitting the papers, authors are strongly encouraged to conduct language editing by native level readers. This will make your paper processing time rather shorter. IJBAS accepts online submission of manuscripts through e-mail to the following email: <a href=\"mailto:editor@insikapub.com\">editor@insikapub.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Format of papers</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAuthors should submit only papers that have been carefully read and polished. Before submission please make sure that your paper is prepared using the <a href=\"http://www.insikapub.com/IJBAS_template_guide/IJBAS_Template.docx\">IJBAS Template</a>. This will ensure fast processing and publication. Acceptance or rejection notification will be sent to all authors.\r\n\r\nThe submission should be accompanied by a cover page showing the author\'s name and address for correspondence (including email), and any acknowledgements. The title should appear on the first page of the manuscript, as IJBAS uses a peer-review process. Therefore, all information revealing the author\'s identity will be removed before we send the paper to the referees. Papers should be submitted in Microsoft Word electronically by e-mail as attachments to the mail id mentioned above.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Article Types</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFour types of manuscripts may be submitted:\r\n<table width=\"450\" align=\"jastify\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Original research</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Survey/ review articles, providing a comprehensive review on a scientific topic.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Short writing: Short, self-contained articles on ongoing research.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Technical Notes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Copyright</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\nSubmission of a manuscript implies: that the work described has not been published before (except in the form of an abstract or as part of a published lecture, or thesis), that it is not under consideration for publication elsewhere. The copyright to articles and figures published in this journal is reserved. When the manuscript is accepted for publication, the authors agree to automatic transfer of the copyright to the publisher.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Review Process</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAll manuscripts are reviewed by an editor and members of the editorial board or qualified outside reviewers. Decisions will be made as early as possible.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Proofs and Reprints</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nElectronic proofs will be sent (as e-mail attachment) to the corresponding author as a PDF file. Page proofs are considered to be the final version of the manuscript.With the exception of typographical or minor clerical errors, no changes will be made in the manuscript at the proof stage, because IJBAS publishes articles online to attract a wide range of audience, authors will have free electronic access to the full text (in both HTML and PDF) of the article. Authors can freely download the PDF file from which they can print unlimited copies of their articles.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Author Fees</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAuthor(s) are required to pay Article Publication Fee of US$ 50 for 10 pages of a manuscript. There are no additional charges for color images. Publication of an article in the IJBAS is not contingent upon the author\'s ability to pay the charges. Neither is acceptance to pay the handling fee guarantees that the paper will be accepted for publication.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAfter properly adjusting with IJBAS Template send your manuscript to: <a href=\"mailto:e